						<summary>

						<p>On the South wall of the central shrine in the Brahmapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīra-Viruppaṇṇa-Uḍaiyar year Pram[ō]dūta.</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete record may be assigned on palaeographical grounds to c. 14th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>The details of date viz., Pramōda, Aṟpaśi 27 are insufficient for verification.</p>						

						<p>The record states that a sum of 25 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> was deposited into the treasury in <hi rend="italic">lieu of</hi> 685 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of different <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> lands sold to Ēṉāttaraipiḷḷai <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Sembiyadaraiyar and Poṉṉāṅkaṭṭi Kāṅgēyar.</p>						

						</summary>
